# Experiment 6: Resource Monitoring – Managed Instance Group with Autoscaling

## Aim
To create an instance template and deploy a Managed Instance Group (MIG) with autoscaling triggered at 60% CPU utilization.

---

## Step 0: Initial Setup
1. Open Google Cloud Console
2. Select the correct Project
3. Ensure billing is enabled

---

## Step 1: Create Instance Template

1. Navigate to:
   Compute Engine → Instance Templates → Create Instance Template

2. Enter configuration:
   - Name: web-template
   - Machine type: e2-micro

3. Allow HTTP traffic:
   - Enable: "Allow HTTP traffic"

4. Go to:
   Management → Automation → Startup Script

5. Paste the script:

```bash
#! /bin/bash
apt-get update -y
apt-get install -y apache2
systemctl start apache2
systemctl enable apache2
Click "Create"

Step 2: Create Managed Instance Group (MIG)
Navigate to:
Compute Engine → Instance Groups → Create Instance Group
Enter:
Name: web-mig
Instance template: web-template
Location: Single zone
Zone: us-central1-a
Set instance limits:
Minimum number of instances: 1
Maximum number of instances: 5

Step 3: Configure Autoscaling
Enable:
Autoscaling: ON
Set:
Autoscaling metric: CPU utilization
Target CPU utilization: 60%
Click "Create"

Step 4: Verify Instance Group
Go to:
Compute Engine → Instance Groups → web-mig
Check:
At least 1 instance is running
Instance is created from template

Step 5: Simulate Load (Optional but Recommended)
Open VM instance from MIG
Click "SSH"
Run:
sudo apt-get install -y stress
stress --cpu 2 --timeout 120

Step 6: Verify Autoscaling
Go to:
Compute Engine → Instance Groups → web-mig
Open:
Monitoring tab
Observe:
CPU usage increases
Number of instances increases (scale out)
After load stops:
Instances decrease (scale in)
----
Shell commands
# 1. Define Variables
export TEMPLATE_NAME="web-template"
export MIG_NAME="web-mig"
export REGION="us-central1"
export ZONE="us-central1-a"

# 2. Create the Instance Template
gcloud compute instance-templates create $TEMPLATE_NAME \
    --machine-type=e2-micro \
    --tags=http-server \
    --metadata=startup-script='#! /bin/bash
apt-get update
apt-get install -y apache2 stress'

# 3. Create the Managed Instance Group (MIG)
gcloud compute instance-groups managed create $MIG_NAME \
    --template=$TEMPLATE_NAME \
    --size=1 \
    --zone=$ZONE

# 4. Set the Autoscaling Policy (60% CPU Target)
gcloud compute instance-groups managed set-autoscaling $MIG_NAME \
    --zone=$ZONE \
    --max-num-replicas=5 \
    --min-num-replicas=1 \
    --target-cpu-utilization=0.60 \
    --cool-down-period=60

# 5. Verification
gcloud compute instance-groups managed describe $MIG_NAME --zone=$ZONE
